Preferred Travel Group (“PTG,” “we,” “us,” or “our”) is committed to protecting the privacy of our customers, hotel guests, members of our
I Prefer
loyalty program, users of the
I Prefer
loyalty program application (“App”) and visitors to our websites,
https://preferredhotels.com
,
https://iprefer.com
, and
https://staybeyondgreen.com
, (the “Sites”) (collectively “Customers”), job applicants, and business-to-business (“B2B”) partners, and through our offline interactions with all of the above(collectively with the Sites and App, the “Services”), which we own and operate as the data controller. This Privacy Policy (“Policy” or “Privacy Policy”) describes how we collect, use, share, and protect information whether collected online or offline and describes your rights. Please note, this Privacy Policy does not govern information we process in our role as a data processor and service provider on behalf of our Member Hotels or that is otherwise collected by our Member Hotels. We partner with hotels to provide you with products and services (“Member Hotels”). Our Member Hotels are independently owned and operated and PTG does not manage or control them or their data practices. For details about our processing of data from Member Hotels (“ Member Hotels Data”), please see the “From Our Member Hotels” section below.
Additionally, please note that
Section I
of this Policy below, which describes our collection and use of information practices through our Services, also serves as our
Notice at Collection for California residents
for purposes of the California Consumer Privacy Act (“CCPA”). Section IA describes our collection and use of information practices for our customers, hotel guests, members of our
I Prefer
loyalty program, users of the App, and visitors to our Sites. Section IB describes our collection and use of information practices for job applicants. Section IC describes our collection and use of information practices in connection with B2B services.
By using our Services, you agree to this Policy. Any changes to this Policy will become effective upon posting of the revised Policy on the Internet, accessible through our Sites and App.
This Policy has been designed to be reasonably accessible to people with disabilities. If you experience any difficulties accessing the information in the Policy, please email us at
Privacy@PreferredHotels.com
.
When we use the term “Personal Information” in this Policy, we mean information that identifies, relates to, describes, is reasonably capable of being associated with, or could reasonably be linked, directly or indirectly, to you or your household. It does not include aggregated, de-identified, or anonymized information that is maintained in a form that is not reasonably capable of being associated with or linked to you. To the extent required by law, we will maintain and use de-identified information in de-identified form and will not attempt to re-identify the information, except to make sure the information is truly de-identified. Any capitalized terms that are not defined shall have the meaning ascribed to them under the applicable law.
Click on any section to expand and view more information:
We collect Personal Information and Other Information. Personal Information includes Sensitive Personal Information.
We collect, use, and disclose Sensitive Personal Information of consumers as necessary to perform the services reasonably expected by an average person and for certain other permitted business purposes. These
permitted
business purposes include helping to perform services reasonably expected by users of the Services who have requested such services, ensuring security and integrity (to the extent the use of the information is reasonably necessary and proportionate for these purposes), ensuring physical safety of natural persons (to the extent the use of the information is reasonably necessary and proportionate for these purposes), short-term, transient use (subject to certain conditions), performing certain services, and engaging in certain activities related to quality or safety of our services or products.
We do not otherwise use or disclose your Sensitive Personal Information.
We will generally store information associated with you until it is no longer necessary to provide services to you, until you ask us to delete it, or until your account, if any, is deleted, whichever comes first; but there are some exceptions to this general rule. We will retain information from deleted accounts to comply with the law, prevent fraud, collect fees, resolve disputes, troubleshoot problems, assist with investigations, enforce our agreements, and take other actions permitted by law. Where we have no continuing purpose to process your Personal Information, we will either delete or anonymize it or, if this is not possible (for example, because your Personal Information has been stored in backup archives), then we will securely store your Personal Information and isolate it from any further processing until deletion is possible. For more information,
contact us
.
